Yoruba Nation agitator Sunday Adeyemo aka Sunday Igboho has narrated how security operatives arrested him in Benin Republic. He said they used his wife, Ropo to arrest him while traveling to Germany last year. Igboho, who is at Cotonou, the Republic of Benin disclosed that he would return back to Nigeria soon. Explaining how he was arrested, he said: “My wife (Ropo) was detained at the (Cadjèhoun) Airport for about two hours. They were ready to hold onto her if I didn’t show up.   UPDATED: Suspected killers of Ahmed Gulak paraded     IPOB declares sit-at-home on Tuesday in Southeast     BREAKING: Buhari swears Ariwoola in as Acting CJN   “Then I showed up and the security agents handcuffed my hands and legs. If I knew that could happen, I wouldn’t allow her to follow me to the airport. “She had already obtained my travelling document from the German government and I would have asked her to go separately but God knew how everything went that way.” Speaking on when he would return back to Nigeria, he said: “I am going back to Nigeria soon.” When asked how soon because the DSS declared him wanted, Igboho referred to the September 2021 judgment by Justice Ladiran Akintola of Oyo High Court which declared the action of the DSS illegal, “arbitrary aggression and prejudices” and awarded N20bn damages against it